articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Trump must remember that the only way to bring home Israeli prisoners is to respect the ceasefire between Israel and Hamas, senior Hamas official Sami Abu Zuhri told Reuters.
articles.title: Ceasefire is only way to bring Israeli prisoners home, Hamas official says

articles.author: Trevor Hunnicutt
articles.description: King Abdullah has said he rejected any moves to annex land and displace Palestinians.
articles.title: Trump and Jordan's king set for tense meeting on Gaza's future

articles.author: Joey Roulette, Eduardo Baptista, Sarah Safty, Joe Brock
articles.description: On the outskirts of Cairo, a cutting-edge space lab was supposed to be the first in Africa to produce homegrown satellites. Step inside the plant, though, and the made-in-Africa image begins to fade
articles.title: China builds space alliances in Africa as Trump cuts foreign aid

articles.author: Ju-Min Park
articles.description: The secretary general of South Korea's National Election Commission defended the integrity of the country's elections on Tuesday amid claims by impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol that votes may have been compromised.
articles.title: South Korea election official rejects impeached president's fraud claims

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Government offices, schools and workplaces fell silent in Sweden at midday on Tuesday in remembrance of the victims of a mass shooting at an adult education centre last week when a gunman killed 10 people before turning his weapon on himself.
articles.title: Sweden honours mass shooting victims and searches for answers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Rwandan-backed M23 rebels in the Democratic Republic of Congo threatened on Tuesday to advance on the provincial capital of Bukavu, citing a "dangerously deteriorating" situation, amid renewed skirmishes on the front line.
articles.title: Congo's Bukavu under threat as M23 rebels warn of intervention

articles.author: Jonathan Allen
articles.description: The novelist Salman Rushdie showed a jury his blinded right eye on Tuesday as he testified against the man charged with trying to murder him at a talk at a rural New York venue in 2022.
articles.title: Novelist Rushdie takes stand in trial of his accused stabber

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: President Donald Trump's administration is not sending U.S. troops into Ukraine, U.S. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth said on Tuesday.
articles.title: U.S. will not send troops to Ukraine, Pentagon chief Hegseth says

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi, Hussam Al-Masri
articles.description: With his Gaza home destroyed in Israel's military offensive, Shaban Shaqaleh was intending to take his family on a break to Egypt once the Hamas-Israel ceasefire is firmly in place.
articles.title: 'Hell worse than what we have already?' Gazans reject Trump plans

articles.author: Ali Sawafta
articles.description: President Mahmoud Abbas faced criticism from allies and foes alike on Tuesday over a decree overhauling payments to families of Palestinians killed or jailed by Israel, a move to satisfy a U.S. demand that will likely deepen his unpopularity.
articles.title: Abbas risks Palestinian backlash over overhaul of prisoner payments
